Restore the f32 reference weight path.

Upstream @ 568ef79 made the runtime W8A8 Q8P-only and removed the f32-dense weight
machinery. The add-on keeps f32 as an optional full-precision reference quant, so
this re-adds a generic (single-threaded, accuracy-reference) f32 arm to each
weight dispatcher in nemotron_asr_kernels.c, the f32 pointer in nemo_weight_t
(nemotron_asr_kernels.h), and the F32 bind in the model loader
(nemotron_asr_model.c). bf16 is not restored.
